{"title_page": "Philip Short", "text_new": "{{about||the former Louisiana state senator | Phil Short|the Irish chess player | Philip Short (chess player)}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2016}}\n'''Philip Short''' (born 17 April 1945) is a British journalist and author.\n\nHe was born in [[Bristol]] on 17 April 1945. He studied at [[Queens' College, Cambridge]]. After graduation, he spent from 1967 to 1973 as a freelance journalist, first in [[Malawi]], then in [[Uganda]]. He then joined the [[BBC]] as a foreign correspondent. He worked there for 25 years.<ref>https://www.davidhigham.co.uk/authors-dh/philip-short/</ref> He is the author of several books, among them the biographies of [[Mao Zedong]], ''[[Mao: A Life]]'' published in 1999, Mao: The Man Who Made China in 2017, [[Pol Pot]], ''[[Pol Pot: Anatomy of a Nightmare]]'', and [[Fran\u00e7ois Mitterrand]], ''A Taste for Intrigue: The Multiple Lives of Fran\u00e7ois Mitterrand''.\n\nHe presented a TV documentary on Mao Zedong entitled \"Mao's Bloody Revolution Revealed\" on the UK terrestrial station [[Five (channel)|Five]] in May 2007.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060912170940/http://www.international.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=21630 Interview] about Pol Pot\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/7893501.stm Video of Short meeting Chinese refugees returning from Vietnam], BBC News video report from August 1978\n*{{C-SPAN|Philip Short}}\n**[https://web.archive.org/web/20160323144121/http://booknotes.org/Watch/155775-1/Philip+Short.aspx ''Booknotes'' interview with Short on ''Mao: A Life'', 2 April 2000.]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Short, Philip}}\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British biographers]]\n[[Category:20th-century biographers]]\n[[Category:21st-century biographers]]\n[[Category:20th-century British male writers]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Queens' College, Cambridge]]\n\n\n{{UK-journalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{about||the former Louisiana state senator | Phil Short|the Irish chess player | Philip Short (chess player)}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2016}}\n'''Philip Short''' (born 17 April 1945) is a British journalist and author.\n\nHe was born in [[Bristol]] on 17 April 1945. He studied at [[Queens' College, Cambridge]]. After graduation, he spent from 1967 to 1973 as a freelance journalist, first in [[Malawi]], then in [[Uganda]]. He then joined the [[BBC]] as a foreign correspondent. He worked there for 25 years.<ref>https://www.davidhigham.co.uk/authors-dh/philip-short/</ref> He is the author of several books, among them the biographies of [[Mao Zedong]], ''[[Mao: A Life]]'' published in 1999, Mao: The Man Who Made China in 2017, [[Pol Pot]], ''[[Pol Pot: Anatomy of a Nightmare]]'', and [[Fran\u00e7ois Mitterrand]], ''A Taste for Intrigue: The Multiple Lives of Fran\u00e7ois Mitterrand''.\n\nHe presented a TV documentary on Mao Zedong entitled \"Mao's Bloody Revolution Revealed\" on the UK terrestrial station [[Five (channel)|Five]] in May 2007.\n\n==References==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060912170940/http://www.international.ucla.edu/article.asp?parentid=21630 Interview] about Pol Pot\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/7893501.stm Video of Short meeting Chinese refugees returning from Vietnam], BBC News video report from August 1978\n*{{C-SPAN|Philip Short}}\n**[https://web.archive.org/web/20160323144121/http://booknotes.org/Watch/155775-1/Philip+Short.aspx ''Booknotes'' interview with Short on ''Mao: A Life'', 2 April 2000.]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Short, Philip}}\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British biographers]]\n[[Category:20th-century biographers]]\n[[Category:21st-century biographers]]\n[[Category:20th-century British male writers]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Queens' College, Cambridge]]\n\n\n{{UK-journalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reflist", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philip_Short"}
{"title_page": "Clyde Kersey", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox officeholder \n| name= Clyde Kersey\n| image name=\n| state_house= Indiana\n| state= Indiana\n| district= 43rd\n| term_start= November 6, 1996\n| term_end=\n| preceded= John Kimmel<ref>http://www.capitolandwashington.com/offices/all-offices/143/</ref>\n| succeeded= \n| party= [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| birth_date= {{birth date and age|1937|11|4|}} \n| birth_place= [[Terre Haute, Indiana]]\n| death_date=\n| death_place=\n| alma_mater= [[Indiana State University]]\n[[Indiana University]]\n| profession= [[Educator]]\n| spouse= Susie\n| residence= [[Terre Haute, Indiana]]\n| religion= [[United Methodist]]\n|}}\n\n'''Clyde R. Kersey''' (born 4 November 1937) is a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] member of the [[Indiana House of Representatives]], representing the 43rd District since 1996. He is also a former member of the Vigo County Council from 1999\u20132004. In 2017, Kersey announced that he would not run for reelection to the State House.<ref>http://indianahousedemocrats.org/state-rep-clyde-kersey-announces-he-will-not-seek-re-election-in-2018/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://indianahousedemocrats.org/clyde-kersey Indiana State Legislature - Representative Clyde Kersey] Official government website\n*[http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=10399 Project Vote Smart - Representative Clyde R. Kersey (IN)] profile\n*''Follow the Money'' - Clyde Kersey\n**[http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=101531 2008] [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=81537 2006] [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=65967 2004] [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=9435 2002] [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=31258 2000] [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=60885 1998] [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/StateGlance/candidate.phtml?c=30997 1996] campaign contributions\n{{Indiana House of Representatives}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kersey, Clyde}}\n[[Category:Members of the Indiana House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:1937 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Terre Haute, Indiana]]\n[[Category:Indiana Democrats]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n\n\n{{Indiana-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{nofootnotes|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox State Representative \n| name= Clyde Kersey\n| image name=\n| state_house= Indiana\n| state= Indiana\n| district= 43rd\n| term_start= November 6, 1996\n| term_end=\n| preceded= John Kimmel<ref>http://www.capitolandwashington.com/offices/all-offices/143/</ref>\n| succeeded= \n| party= [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| birth_date= {{birth date and age|1937|11|4|}} \n| birth_place= [[Terre Haute, Indiana]]\n| death_date=\n| death_place=\n| alma_mater= [[Indiana State University]]\n[[Indiana University]]\n| profession= [[Educator]]\n| spouse= Susie\n| residence= [[Terre Haute, Indiana]]\n| religion= [[United Methodist]]\n|}}\n\n'''Clyde R. Kersey''' (born 4 November 1937) is a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] member of the [[Indiana House of Representatives]], representing the 43rd District since 1996. He is also a former member of the Vigo County Council from 1999\u20132004. In 2017, Kersey announced that he would not run for reelection to the State House.<ref>http://indianahousedemocrats.org/state-rep-clyde-kersey-announces-he-will-not-seek-re-election-in-2018/</ref>\n\n==External links==\n*[http://indianahousedemocrats.org/clyde-kersey Indiana State Legislature - Representative Clyde Kersey] Official government website\n*[http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=10399 Project Vote Smart - Representative Clyde R. Kersey (IN)] profile\n*''Follow the Money'' - Clyde Kersey\n**[http://www.followthem