ance-plus-3-see-photos-4814378/ |title=Dancing legend Govinda steals the show with his latka jhatka on Dance Plus 3. See photos |publisher=indianexpress.com}}</ref>''\n|[[Star Plus]]\n|Captain\n|- \n|2018 \n|''[[Dance Plus (season 4)|Dance Plus 4]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/sugandha-mishra-to-host-dance-plus-4/articleshow/65923571.cms/ |title=Sugandha Mishra to host 'Dance Plus 4' \n|publisher=timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref>''\n|[[Star Plus]]\n|Captain\n|-\n|2020\n|[[Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi 10|''Khatron Ke Khiladi 10'']]\n|[[Colors TV]]\n|Contestant\n|-\n|2020\n|[[Dance Plus (season 5)|Dance Plus 5]]\n|[[StarPlus|Star Plus]]\n|Winning Captain\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n===As an actor===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 100%;\"\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Movie\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role \n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2013 || [[ABCD : AnyBody Can Dance|ABCD : Any Body Can Dance]] || Dharmesh/D || Lead role with [[Prabhu Deva]], [[Kay Kay Menon]], [[Ganesh Acharya]], [[Punit Pathak]],\n[[Salman Yusuff Khan]], [[Lauren Gottlieb]].\n|-\n| 2015 || [[ABCD 2]] || Dharmesh/D || Lead role with [[Varun Dhawan]], [[Shraddha Kapoor]] and [[Prabhu Deva]], [[Punit Pathak]],\n[[Lauren Gottlieb]], [[Raghav Juyal]].\n|-\n| 2016 || [[Banjo (2016 film)]] || Grease || with [[Riteish Deshmukh]]\n|-\n| 2018 || [[Nawabzaade]]  || Salim ||  with [[Punit Pathak]] and [[Raghav Juyal]]\n|-\n| 2020 ||[[Street Dancer (film)|Street Dancer]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/street-dancer-varun-dhawan-kicks-off-the-london-schedule-of-the-film-in-style-312957.htm|title=Street Dancer: Varun Dhawan kicks off second schedule of the film in snowy London|website=in.com|access-date=2019-02-14}}</ref>|| D || with [[Varun Dhawan]] [[Shraddha Kapoor]] [[ Punit Pathak]] [[Raghav Juyal]] [[ Prabhu Deva]] [[ Shakti Mohan]] and [[Nora Fatehi]]\n|}\n\n===As a choreographer===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 100%;\"\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Movie name\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010 || [[Tees Maar Khan (2010 film)|''Tees Maar Khan'']] || He choreographed the title song for Akshay Kumar.\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=3797588}}\n*{{facebook|id=DharmeshSir}}\n*[https://getwikibio.com/dharmesh-yelande/ Dharmesh Yelande] Full [https://getwikibio.com/ Wiki Bio]\n\n{{Dance India Dance}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yelande, Dharmesh}}\n[[Category:Indian choreographers]]\n[[Category:Indian male dancers]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Dancers from Gujarat]]\n[[Category:Hip hop dancers]]\n[[Category:Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi participants]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{short description|Indian dancer and choreographer}}\n{{fanpov|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Dharmesh Yelande \n| image              = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1983|10|31|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Baroda]], [[Gujarat]], [[India]]\n| nationality        = [[Indian people|Indian]]\n| occupation         = [[Dancer]], [[Choreographer]], [[Actor]]\n}}\n'''Dharmesh Yelande''' (born 31 October 1983) also known as '''Dharmesh Sir''' participated in ''[[Dance India Dance (season 2)]]'', ''[[Dance India Dance Li'l Masters]]'' (as a skipper), and [[Dance Ke Superstars]], all of which aired on [[Zee TV]]. After his experience in these shows, he was hired by [[Farah Khan]] to choreograph the movie ''[[Tees Maar Khan (2010 film)|Tees Maar Khan]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3797588/|title=Dharmesh Yelande&nbsp;\u2014 works|publisher=IMDb|accessdate=2011-07-14}}</ref>  He has worked in the 3D dance-based Indian film [[AnyBody Can Dance - ABCD|ABCD \u2013 Anybody Can Dance]], its sequel [[ABCD 2]] and [[ABCD 3]]  with [[Shraddha Kapoor]] and [[Varun Dhawan]] directed by [[Remo D'souza]] and produced by [[UTV Motion Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/uncategorized/utv-signs-reality-show-talents-for-3d-dance-film_100560980.html|title=DUTV signs reality show talents for 3D dance film|publisher=Thaindian|accessdate=2011-10-20}}</ref> He runs his own dance academy in Vadodara known as the ''D'virus Dance Academy''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dthevirus.blogspot.com//|title=D'virus Academy|publisher=Blogger|accessdate=2011-07-14}}</ref> Dharmesh also worked as a dancer in Marathi movie ''Angarki'' in 2013.<ref>http://www.bollywoodsamay.com/2016/07/%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B6-%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%A1%E0%A5%87-%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%80-%E0%A4%9C%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%80/</ref>. He has worked in the film [[Banjo (2016 film)|Banjo]] opposite Riteish Deshmukh and Nargis Fakhri. He has been a mentor in all the five seasons of the dance reality show [[Dance Plus|Dance plus]] along with [[Shakti Mohan]] and [[Sumeet Nagdev]] ([[Dance Plus (season 1)|season 1]]), [[Punit Pathak]] (from [[Dance Plus (season 2)|2nd season]]),  Karishma Chavan and Suresh Mukund ([[Dance Plus (season 5)|season 5]])\n\n== Inspiration ==\nHis inspiration for dance is [[Remo D'Souza|Remo D\u2019souza]], according to his remarks in the DID audition, he says, \"Remo Sir is also a mindblowing dancer. Whenever I meet him, it's only dance that we discuss. He's a person with such wonderful dance techniques that one is left simply wondering \u2018Ki kya idea hai bhai, yeh step to dhoom macha dega\".<ref name=\"SpellCeleb\" /> He himself is a big inspiration to many budding dancers.\n\n== Achievements ==\nHe has won the dance show,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/were-not-celebrities-were-still-locals-dharmesh-raghav/articleshow/59513071.cms |title=We're not celebrities, we're still locals: Dharmesh, Raghav |publisher=timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref> [[Boogie Woogie (TV series)]]<ref name=SpellCeleb>{{cite web|title=Dharmesh Yelande Biography|url=http://spellceleb.com/dharmesh-sir-or-dharmesh-yelande-wiki-did-journey-movies-dance-style-tv-shows-choreographer-idol-interview/|website=spellceleb.com|accessdate=12 July 2015}}</ref> and was first runner-up on [[Dance India Dance (season 2)]].<ref name=SpellCeleb/> He starred in [[ABCD : AnyBody Can Dance]], [[ABCD 2]] and he choreographed for the movie [[Tees Maar Khan (2010 film)|Tees Maar Khan]].\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 100%;\"\n|+\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Show \n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Channel \n! style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Krazzy Kiya Re|Airtel Krazzy Kiya Re]]'' || [[DD National]] || Runner-up \n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Boogie Woogie (TV series)]] Mahayudh'' || [[Sony Entertainment Television]] || Winner.\n|-\n| 2009\u20132010 || ''[[Dance India Dance (season 2)]]'' || [[Zee TV]] || Runner-up \n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Dance India Dance Li'l Masters]]'' || [[Zee TV]] || Jeetumoni (Team Dharmesh) \n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Comedy Ka Daily Soap|Comedy ka Daily Soap]]'' || [[Sony Entertainment Television]] || Guest performance.\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Zee Rishtey Awards]]'' || [[Zee TV]] || Guest performance\n|- \n| 2010\u20132011 || ''[[DID Doubles]]'' || [[Zee TV]] || Assisted mentor [[Geeta Kapoor]] and choreographed some of the gems from the season.\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Dance Ke Superstars]]'' || [[Zee TV]] || Winner of the show.\n|-\n| 2011 || ''Dhamaal Night'' || [[Zee Cinema]] || Guest performance.\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Just Dance (Indian TV series)|Just Dance]]'' || [[Star Plus]] || He choreographed the final performance of Hrithik Roshan and some other performances in the show.\n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Dance Ke Superkids]]'' || [[